# Design Token Naming

- Prefer reusable design-system token names over feature/state-specific names.
- Do not create tokens tied to a page, component, or flow (for example `chat-*`, `members-*`, `invite-*`).
- Avoid naming base color tokens as states (for example `success`, `warning`) unless they are semantic aliases mapped from base tokens.

## Naming Model

- Base hue tokens (reusable): `--color-green`, `--color-amber`
- Role variants from base hues: `--color-green-fg`, `--color-green-bg-subtle`
- Optional semantic aliases can map to base hues when needed (for example `--state-success-fg: var(--color-green-fg)`).

## Rules

- New component styles should consume existing global tokens first.
- If a new token is needed, define it in `public/global.css` as a reusable system token.
- Keep naming generic and composable so tokens can be reused across unrelated UI.
